ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: I experience myself as separate from my changing thoughts and feelings.
Notes: 0 = Not at all ; 1 = A little ; 2 = Moderately; 3 = Quite a bit ; 4 = Very Much ; 999 = Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: I am more concerned with being open to my experiences than controlling or changing them.
Notes: 0 = Not at all ; 1 = A little ; 2 = Moderately; 3 = Quite a bit ; 4 = Very Much ; 999 = Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: I am curious about what I might learn about myself by taking notice of how I react to certain thoughts, feelings or sensations.
Notes: 0 = Not at all ; 1 = A little ; 2 = Moderately; 3 = Quite a bit ; 4 = Very Much ; 999 = Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: I experience my thoughts more as events in my mind than as a necessarily accurate reflection of the way things 'really' are.
Notes: 0 = Not at all ; 1 = A little ; 2 = Moderately; 3 = Quite a bit ; 4 = Very Much ; 999 = Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: I am curious to see what my mind is up to from moment to moment.
Notes: 0 = Not at all ; 1 = A little ; 2 = Moderately; 3 = Quite a bit ; 4 = Very Much ; 999 = Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: I am curious about each of my thoughts and feelings as they occur.
Notes: 0 = Not at all ; 1 = A little ; 2 = Moderately; 3 = Quite a bit ; 4 = Very Much ; 999 = Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: I am receptive to observing unpleasant thoughts and feelings without interfering with them.
Notes: 0 = Not at all ; 1 = A little ; 2 = Moderately; 3 = Quite a bit ; 4 = Very Much ; 999 = Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: I am more invested in just watching my experiences as they arise, than in figuring out what they could mean.
Notes: 0 = Not at all ; 1 = A little ; 2 = Moderately; 3 = Quite a bit ; 4 = Very Much ; 999 = Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: I approach each experience by trying to accept it, no matter whether it is pleasant or unpleasant.
Notes: 0 = Not at all ; 1 = A little ; 2 = Moderately; 3 = Quite a bit ; 4 = Very Much ; 999 = Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: I remain curious about the nature of each experience as it arises.
Notes: 0 = Not at all ; 1 = A little ; 2 = Moderately; 3 = Quite a bit ; 4 = Very Much ; 999 = Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: I am aware of my thoughts and feelings without over-identifying with them.
Notes: 0 = Not at all ; 1 = A little ; 2 = Moderately; 3 = Quite a bit ; 4 = Very Much ; 999 = Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: I am curious about my reactions to things.
Notes: 0 = Not at all ; 1 = A little ; 2 = Moderately; 3 = Quite a bit ; 4 = Very Much ; 999 = Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: I am curious about what I might learn about myself by just taking notice of what my attention gets drawn to.
Notes: 0 = Not at all ; 1 = A little ; 2 = Moderately; 3 = Quite a bit ; 4 = Very Much ; 999 = Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: TMS Total score
Notes: Sum total of all 13 items on scale

ElementDescription: TMS Average Score
Notes: Mean of all 13 items on scale

ElementDescription: TMS Curiosity Total score
Notes: Total of Scale items tms_3, tms_5, tms_6, tms_10, tms_12, tms_13

ElementDescription: TMS Curiosity Average score
Notes: Divide Curiosity Total score by the curiosity items (6) to get average

ElementDescription: TMS Decentering Total Score
Notes: Total of Scale items tms_1, tms_2, tms_4, tms_7, tms_8, tms_9, tms_11

ElementDescription: TMS Decentering Average Score
Notes: Divide Decentering Total score by the decentering items (7) to get average
